r a drops / mob list of the items required for this quest? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ujonoisgod.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jonoisgod</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/22/01 6:01:49 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re:6th Shawl info request</span><hr size=1> Here's everything I know.  I have not finished it, but I have failed 4 times so I am damn close to finishing it.<br>
<br>
First off, head to great divide.  Go to the spires near the east wastes zone, and med there.  Many wolves will come by, I find the easiest way to kill them is just draught them once to get their attention, then draught them again and they are dead.  You will need 2 whiskers which are very rare, I'd say about 1 in 20.<br>
<br>
Next, go slaughter all the giants you can in the zone.  They range from about 35-45, and none are very tough, very easily kited.  Rare drop is a beard, you can also find them on vendors for 150p or auction for one for about 50p.<br>
<br>
Next, we get to go to east wastes and kill manticores.  They roam throughout the zone, have about 4,000 hps.  They are roughly level 38, lil tough for their level but nothing unkitable.  They commonly hang out near the great divide zone, auction for their manes offering 50p a piece as you kill them, they will drop one every 2 kills or so.<br>
<br>
Last part is the hardest.  Port over to Cobaltscar.  If you are not at least 50, do not try this solo, at 53 I still get raped by the sirens.  I find it easiest to do with a caster partner that is working on the quest also.  Head over to the skyshrine tower, buff up to the max and if possible get magic resistance buff from nearby druid/enchanter/cleric.  Put on every single piece of magic resistance gear you have, you will need at least 100+ to even stand a chance.  As you look over the edge, you will see 3 sirens down on the beach.  There are 3 different types, enticers (roughly level 35, 2000-2500 hps), seductresses (roughly level 40, 4000-4500 hps) and enchantreses (roughly level 45, 6000-6500 hps).  Enticers are easily soloed by a 53 wiz, I'm sure any wiz over 45 could kill one solo.  Seductresses are a hard fight, I will win about 70% of the time if I am prepared.  Enchantresses are impossible to solo, they are just too hard.  The key to fighting these is chain stunning them.  They will dispell/nuke/charm you, all which hurt bad.  They seem to be easily single pulled if there are 2 greens, otherwise just ask someone in the zone for help.  They drop many items: siren parts for baking, the hair for the quest (about a 1 in 20 drop), a bard horn, scales for a kael bag quest, and a necklace that has 5 charges of enduring breath which is also used for 7th shawl.<br>
<br>
Happy hunting, bring friends for sirens <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udiomedes.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Diomedes</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/23/01 7:04:12 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re:6th Shawl info request</span><hr size=1> note - the runed seashell necklace is *NOT* used for the 7th shawl quest. You need to get a *runed sea shell* off sirens in sirens grotto. The main difference between the 2 - aside from one being a simple runed seashell the other being a runed seashell necklace) is that the one you want only has *1* charge of EB (the other has 5 charges).<br>
<br>
Im raising tailoring to attempt 6th shawl atm... but ive got all the pieces for the 7th shawl in the bank.<br>
<br>
Get yourself into an SG castle group and head from WW zone down the well. Trickiest part of getting to this area is the initial fight in the well - if you arent careful you could have as many as 6 mobs to fight at the same time. Once in the castle area it wont be long until you have a runed seashell and a molkor hide.<br>
<br>
good luck! <p><font face="verdana" size="2">[60 Sorcerer] <a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=85843" target="new"><b>Diomedes</b></a></font> (High Elf) <font face="verdana" size="2">
